<?xml version='1.0' encoding='UTF-8'?>
<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-06-23T05:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-06-23T05:00:00-05:00" n="293" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d293">
                                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00119 Control (<persName corresp="#p_R3">Rumania</persName>)/6–2345: Telegram</note>
                                <head>No. 293<lb/><hi rend="italic">The Acting Representative in
                                            <persName corresp="#p_R3">Rumania</persName>
                                    </hi> (<persName corresp="#p_MRM1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Melbourne</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the
                                            <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of State</gloss>
                                    </hi>
                                </head>
                                <opener>
                                    <seg rendition="#left">
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                                        <lb/>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">us urgent</hi>
                                    </seg>
                                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                                        <placeName>
                                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Bucharest</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-06-23T12:00:00+02:00">June 23, 1945—noon</date>.</dateline>
                                </opener>
                                <p>430. The Brit political representative<note n="1" xml:id="d293fn1">
                                        <persName corresp="#p_LJH1">J. H. Le
                                        Rougetel</persName>.</note> and Mr. <persName corresp="#p_BBY1">Berry</persName> discussed the question of
                                    a possible peace treaty with <persName corresp="#p_R3">Rumania</persName> before the latter’s departure for the US
                                        (<gloss target="#t_Dept1">Dept</gloss>’s 310, June 21<note n="2" xml:id="d293fn2">See <ref target="#d290fn1">document
                                            No. 290, footnote 1</ref>.</note>). Since he is
                                    scheduled to arrive in the US within a day or two of this
                                    telegram it is felt that <gloss target="#t_Dept1">Dept</gloss>
                                    may wish to gain Mr. <persName corresp="#p_BBY1">Berry</persName>’s personal views.<note n="3" xml:id="d293fn3">No memorandum reflecting <persName corresp="#p_BBY1">Berry</persName>’s views on this
                                        subject has been found.</note>
                                    <gloss target="#t_rptd1">Rptd</gloss> Moscow as 114 and London
                                    as 1.</p>
                                <p>Upon Genl <persName corresp="#p_SBGCTVR1">Schuyler</persName>’s
                                    return from an inspection trip in three days I will suggest to
                                    him that he may wish to present his views by telegram reflecting
                                    his experience upon the <gloss target="#t_ACC1">ACC</gloss>.<note n="4" xml:id="d293fn4">See <ref target="#d299">documents Nos. 299</ref> and <ref target="#d300">300</ref>.</note>
                                </p>
                                <closer>
                                    <signed>
                                        <persName corresp="#p_MRM1">
                                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Melbourne</hi>
                                        </persName>
                                    </signed>
                                </closer>
                            </div>
                            </body></text></TEI>